The Walking Dead: The Ones Who Liveâ€™ trailer Unveils Michonne's quest for Rick in a post-apocalyptic world

etimes.in / Jan 11, 2024, 14:12 (IST)

The trailer for 'The Walking Dead: The Ones Who Live' has been released, building anticipation for its February 25 premiere. Andrew Lincoln and Danai Gurira return as Rick and Michonne, who face the challenges of a war against the dead and the living. In the trailer, Michonne searches for Rick in a desolate wasteland, held captive by the enigmatic Alliance of the Three. Terry O'Quinn joins the cast as Major General Beale and Pollyanna McIntosh reprises her role as Jadis. The official description teases an epic love story and the unraveling of their existence in a gripping tale of survival.

'Vikings: Valhalla' to end with season 3

ANI / Oct 07, 2023, 16:57 (IST)

'Vikings: Valhalla', the popular drama series, is gearing up for its final act with the third season, set to release in 2024. This series, created by Jeb Stuart, stands as a follow-up to Michael Hirst's original 'Vikings'. Following its 2022 premiere, it quickly received a two-season extension. Set in the early 11th century, the show delves into the enthralling tales of legendary Vikings like Leif Eriksson (Sam Corlett), Freydis Eriksdotter (Frida Gustavsson), Harald Hardrada (Leo Suter), and Norman King William the Conqueror, illustrating their struggles and endeavors in a dynamic world.
